column1: Observed Geomagnetic Storm Parameters:Max Kp: 6.0Dst min. in nT: -87 Dst min. time: 2015-11-07T08:00Z  CME Note: CME is connected to a M3.7 flare at AR 12443 very close to disk center, GOES light curve is a long duration event, with extensive post-event loops visible in AIA 131. Large, fast wave emanating from flare site, dimming to the west and north of the AR in AIA 193, dark absorption material ejected at west end of AR seen in AIA 304
